channel.title: Keyboard stopped working?
channel.description: The other day I was using my laptop, and I was in the middle of typing an English essay and my HG' and backspace key stopped working? (I'm using onscreen keyboard) I was just wondering why it quick working all of a sudden, would I have to take it in to be fixed? Or could I possibly replace it myself?

item.title: Keyboard stopped working?
item.dc:creator: @SilentCJ SilentCJ
item.description:
@SilentCJ wrote:

Have you spilt any liquid on it at all? Even a drip?
This happened to my girlfriend’s, some of the key’s just wouldn’t do anything, and others would just type any random letter (pressing R would type a question mark, for example).

item.title: Keyboard stopped working?
item.dc:creator: @xxx123xxx xxx123xxx
item.description:
@xxx123xxx wrote:

CoonHunter:

Might need a replacement keyboard. This has happened on every laptop i have owned. Usually a replacement keyboard fixed it.

Also, a keyboard on a laptop is usually easy to replace if you look at a disassembly guide for your specific model before hand

item.description:

Do you press your keys hard or have you dropped your laptop recently?
